    "ideation": "The goal net animation is a story of anticipation, impact, and the lingering vibration of the twine. The face acts as the net itself. The eyes represent the tension points where the net is staked: initially wide and watchful, anticipating the shot. When the ball hits, the eyes collapse inward to show the physical displacement of the mesh, and the mouth—the literal net line—surges into a frantic high-frequency wave to mimic the kinetic energy of a scoring strike. As the ball drops, the tension releases into a slow, swaying recovery ripple before returning to a steady, ready state. The colors move from a focused white to a vibrant, triumphant goal-gold, then settle back into a professional 'pitch green'.",
